h3. Problem Definition

With the upcoming [deprecation of usernames|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/blog/2018/06/say-goodbye-to-usernames-in-atlassian-cloud] in Jira cloud, the rest api endpoint for User can only be queried using AccountID. 

h3. Suggested Solution

Allow the user endpoint operations to be queried using email address.

{code}
https://<jira_site>/rest/api/3/user?emailAddress=<email address>
{code}

h3. Why this is important
 
Users should be able to use the endpoint on a single query with a known parameter. 

h3. Workaround 

Use the user search endpoint with the email address to get the self URL.

{code}
GET https://<jira_site>/rest/api/3/user/search?query=<email address>
{code}

The self URL returned can further be used for other operations such as delete. 

{code}
DELETE https://<jira_site>/rest/api/3/user?username=<username>
{code}

h3. Summary
Cannot successfully call the REST API [Update comment|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v2/#api-api-2-issue-issueIdOrKey-comment-id-put] without the body even if the documentation says it is not required.

See Jira Cloud Issue Comment update REST API docs (https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v2/#api-api-2-issue-issueIdOrKey-comment-id-put) that say:
{quote}
body (string)
The comment. Required on create, optional for update.
{quote}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Update a comment with the following request body {code}{
  "visibility": {
    "type": "role",
    "value": "Administrators"
  }
}{code}

h3. Expected Results
Successful comment update

h3. Actual Results
HTTP status 400
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [],
    "errors": {
        "comment": "Comment body can not be empty!"
    }
}
{code}

h3. Notes
REST API fails for both v2 and v3

h3. Summary

When trying to get context parameters thru AP.context.getContext(), no response is returned immediately. Repeating calls were made to AP.context one per 5 seconds. First several results didn't have the issue key, and context was an empty object. Issue key appeared after 30 seconds only:
 !TST board - Agile Board - JIRA 2018-09-14 22-44-50.png|thumbnail! 

API is invoked when frame is loaded an script starts working:

{code}
export function getIssueKey() {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =>{
        try {
            AP.context.getContext(
                context => {
                    const issueKey = access('jira.issue.key', context)
                    if (issueKey) {
                        // console.log('issue key is resolved', issueKey)
                        resolve(issueKey)
                    } else {
                        //console.log('issue key is not resolved', context)

                        // I noticed that context is an empty object in this case,
                        // try to get issueKey from URL parameters:
                        const params = getQueryParams(location.search)
                        resolve(params['issue.key'])
                    }
                }
            )
        } catch(e) {
            reject(e)
        }
    })
}
{code}

h3. Notes
- Works in old issue view
- iframe is nor cacheable
- Not sure if this is by design

h3. Summary

Wen trying to access some filters, in the "Issues and Filters", inside a project, returns the below error.

!Error.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Steps to Reproduce

To reproduce:
# Hide the priority field in a project
# Access backlog view;
# Click on Issues and Filters;
# Click on "All Issues" or "My Open Issues" or "Open Issues";
# Error is displayed.

*Expected:* It will return the issues based on the chosen filter.

*Actual:* It returns an error, not showing the issues.
The error below returns to the following request in browser:
{code}
https://instance.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/search?startAt=0&maxResults=50&jql=project%20=%20%22ABC%22%20ORDER%20BY%20priority%20DESC&fields=summary,status,issuetype,assignee
{code}
{code}
{"errorMessages":["Not able to sort using field 'priority'."],"warningMessages":[]}
{code}

h3. Workaround
Unhide the field Priority, by clicking "Show" in the field configuration.

h3. Summary

When creating tabs in an app via:

{code}
"jiraIssueTabPanels": [
    {
        "key": "action-step-issue-association-panel",
        "name": {
            "value": "Anne 0"
        },
        "url": "/hello-world?issueId={issue.id}&projectId={project.id}",
        "layout": {
            "width": "70%"
        },

        "location": "atl.jira.view.issue.left.context",
        "weight": 250
    },
    {
        "key": "action-step-issue-association-panel-1",
        "name": {
            "value": "Anne 1"
        },
        "url": "/hello-world?issueId={issue.id}&projectId={project.id}",
        "layout": {
            "width": "70%"
        },
        "location": "atl.jira.view.issue.left.context",
        "weight": 250
    }
],
{code}

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

Selecting the first tab is loaded:
 !screenshot-4.png|thumbnail! 

but succeeding selections results in error message (after ~3s): "We're having trouble connecting to Associated Issues. Try contacting the developer for support." 

 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 
 !screenshot-3.png|thumbnail! 

Unlike the old view, the tabs are loaded successfully. One difference is, when switching between tabs the page is refreshed for each click.

h3. Expectation
You can switch freely between app tabs, comments and contents are loaded

h3. Workaround
None

With the new board layout in the Jira Cloud Web application, there are not sufficient keyboard shortcuts to quickly navigate a Kanban or Scrum board for a sprint in progress.

For instance, accessing the Assignee dropdown via keyboard would allow very quick filtering to a specific person, e.g.
{noformat}
Shift+A, jane, Enter{noformat}
Similarly, clearing the Assignee selector, e.g.
{noformat}
Shift+A, Space{noformat}
Also, focusing the search filter field already present purely via keyboard, e.g.
{noformat}
Shift+F{noformat}
Also, accessing the Quick Filters dropdown via keyboard for quick typeahead, e.g.
{noformat}
Shift+Q{noformat}
Bonus points if the keyboard shortcuts are customizable, but any shortcuts that don’t require incessant mouse clicking will greatly speed up Standups and project managers’ lives.
